parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not be adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the driver or passenger hits their head on the steering wheel or dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective airbag sensor can cause the airbag to malfunction or not deploy in a crash, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the airbag sensor is diagnosed as defective
the airbag may not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to shut down without warning, leading to a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: power steering and power brakes are lost
the car is completely dead with no response when the ignition key is turned

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random misfire and engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, vibrate, and stall, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the check engine light flashes or stays on
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges in speed without pressing the accelerator
the engine continues to rev even after shifting into neutral
the vehicle is slow to reach minimum speed
the vehicle rolls backward or stops on hills.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty throttle cable and throttle body can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the engine continues to rev even after shifting into neutral

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty catalytic converter can cause reduced vehicle performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially toxic fuel emissions, which can be hazardous to drivers and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle is loud and slow
the vehicle rolls backward or stops on hills
the vehicle is slow to reach minimum speed
the vehicle cuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.

the engine makes a knocking sound

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
